synonyms: nava—newly grown; nimba-patra—nimba leaves; saha—along with; bhṛṣṭa-vārtākī—fried eggplant; phula-baḍī—light baḍī; paṭola-bhājā—fried paṭola vegetable; kuṣmāṇḍa—of pumpkin; māna—of squash; cākī—rounds.
translation: Other preparations included eggplant mixed with newly grown nimba leaves fried together, light baḍī, fried paṭola, and fried rounds of squash and pumpkin.
